::Part I::<br>
<br>
The auburn hair of the human child clung to her bare back and chest.  Her young body, barely 12 winters, was covered in sweat.  Meditating she found her center, meditating she found herself.  A sudden stab of pain snapped her out of her meditation.  She silently cursed herself for allowing the distraction to break her introspection.<br>
<br>
Bringing her hands up to her face, she sighed and wiped  the sweat from her eyes.  The scent and tang of copper stung her senses, she pulled her hands down and stared at them in horror.  Blood covered her hands, panic struck her and she stood to find the source of it.  She cried out, the sharp pain in her legs tore through her.  looking down she saw the fine cuts in her legs, the seemingly random marks she made with the blade.  The blade that lay in front of her.<br>
<br>
The blade was carved from veined obsidian, it held shadows to it like the scales of a reptile, the edges of the blade jagged and wicked.  It's pommel decorated with runes she could not recognize.  The weapon lay in a pool of blood and seemed to drink it into itself.   she watched in horror as the blood began to disappear.<br>
<br>
Her mind raced as she struggled to remember ever seeing the blade preciously.  She tried to understand why she would have done this to herself.  The door to her chamber burst open.  Her father rushed in, &quot;I heard your cries, what is it Alandrial?!&quot;  His voice was laced with panic, he gasped at seeing her, in this condition.  Turning toward's him she offered him her arms, her hands reaching for him.  The look on her face, a broken child.  &quot;Daddy&quot; she barely whispered before her body collapsed to the floor, before he could take his first step.<br>
<br>
The candle light in her room stung her eyes as she awoke.  Looking around she recognized her own room and calmed herself, wanting to listen for the sound of her own breath.  She could hear her breathing, she could also hear the whispered voices outside her door.  A strange voice she did not know whispered quietly but firmly, &quot;...my knowledge of the language...definitely dark...sign of taint...&quot;  She struggled to listen close, now she could her her mother weeping softly.  her father's strong voice carried easily, &quot;...understand Brother, she will be...&quot;  the pause was impossibly painful and impossibly long &quot;...will be turned over to the Temple to be exorcised of this taint.&quot;<br>
<br>
Her breath caught in her throat.  Alandrial knew too well the horrors of the Inquisition of Mithaniel Marr.  She knew of the death that was promised to the unclean.  The ultimate cleansing of the soul.  <br>
<br>
Panic ripped through her mind, tore away at her calm and thrust her into blind fear.  She sprung out of bed, stiffling a cry of pain she ran to her window.  She leapt from the window, as she landed something tore, something that should not have on her landing.  A whimper escaped her lips as she made her way into the darkness.<br>
<br>
The world around Alandrial was not hers.  Pain was the only thing she knew.  Picking her way through the alien landscape she saw the world shrinking before her, the darkness enclosing around the edges of her vision.  She stumbled a bit further before she lost consciousness.<br>
<br>
